   1: # Clinical domain scope template — HONEST-REBUILD Phase 2c.
   2: #
   3: # Used when the user is researching drug efficacy, safety, mechanism,
   4: # clinical guidelines, meta-analyses, or treatment comparisons. The
   5: # corpus should be dominated by peer-reviewed primary studies (T1)
   6: # and systematic reviews (T2), with regulatory documents (T3) as the
   7: # authoritative source for labelled indications and safety warnings.
   8: #
   9: # Industry marketing / HCP-portal sources (T5) are allowed but capped
  10: # at <=15% and must not dominate any section. Commentary / blog (T6)
  11: # and conference abstracts / preprints (T7) are allowed only as
  12: # supporting or hypothesis-generating evidence.
  13: 
  14: domain: clinical
  15: description: >
  16:   Peer-reviewed-primary-evidence-dominant corpus for clinical research.
  17:   Follows PRISMA-style inclusion / exclusion patterns.
  18: 
  19: # Default PICO framing overrides. The scope gate will attempt heuristic
  20: # extraction from the query first; these are fallback defaults.
  21: pico_defaults:
  22:   comparator: placebo or standard of care
  23: 
  24: # Inclusion criteria surfaced to the user in the pre-registered protocol.
  25: inclusion_criteria:
  26:   - Peer-reviewed journal article indexed in PubMed / OpenAlex / Semantic Scholar.
  27:   - Human studies.
  28:   - Published in English, or with a certified English translation.
  29:   - Reports quantitative outcomes (efficacy, safety, PK/PD, or QoL).
  30:   - Regulatory documents (FDA/EMA/Health Canada/MHRA/TGA/PMDA/NMPA) when
  31:     discussing labelled indications, contraindications, or safety warnings.
  32: 
  33: # Exclusion criteria surfaced to the user in the pre-registered protocol.
  34: exclusion_criteria:
  35:   - User-upload document hosts (Scribd, SlideShare, ResearchGate) unless
  36:     the document is also available at the original issuer's URL.
  37:   - Student journals (high school journals, undergraduate journals).
  38:   - Press releases from pharmaceutical manufacturers without a peer-reviewed
  39:     primary source to corroborate claims.
  40:   - Blog posts and law-firm commentary used as primary evidence (allowed as
  41:     supplementary context only).
  42:   - In vitro and animal-only studies when the research question is human-
  43:     clinical (allowed for mechanistic sections only).
  44: 
  45: # Expected final-corpus tier distribution. The corpus-approval gate
  46: # (Phase 2g) checks actual retrieval against this and shows the delta
