  66:       are authoritative for labelled indications and safety warnings.
  67:   - tier: T4
  68:     min_fraction: 0.00
  69:     max_fraction: 0.20
  70:     rationale: >
  71:       Narrative reviews and clinical guideline articles — useful for
  72:       context and mechanism, but not for novel efficacy claims.
  73:   - tier: T5
  74:     min_fraction: 0.00
  75:     max_fraction: 0.15
  76:     rationale: >
  77:       Industry HCP portals and marketing pages — allowed for labelled
  78:       claims that are already corroborated by T3 regulatory sources.
  79:   - tier: T6
  80:     min_fraction: 0.00
  81:     max_fraction: 0.10
  82:     rationale: >
  83:       Commentary, news, and blog posts — allowed only as context,
  84:       not as primary evidence.
  85:   - tier: T7
  86:     min_fraction: 0.00
  87:     max_fraction: 0.10
  88:     rationale: >
  89:       Conference abstracts and preprints — hypothesis-generating only.
  90:       Should not dominate a systematic review corpus.
